		<br>
		<p>BC Centre for Disease Control, 100,000 square feet building is the state of art clinical and research facility. The building contains three separate level 3 laboratories (special pathogens, HIV and tuberculosis).</p>

		<p>CES Engineering was hired by BC Building Corporation to provide laboratories design management, DDC control design, commissioning and certification services. Our scope of work for this project included following services:
		<ol>
			<li>
				<ul>Management of the design process for the CL 3 laboratories by performing the following services:
					<li>Acting as a liaison between user group, design team, construction group and PHAC/CFIA representatives</li>
					<li>Consultation and advice to the design team for specialty laboratory containment practices</li>
					<li>Performing a focused review of the laboratories design and construction documents with reference to PHAC/CFIA Certification requirements for level 3 laboratories. The review includes complete laboratory design including all architectural, electrical and mechanical services and Owner equipment</li>
					<li>Incorporation of the CL 3 certification process into specification documents</li>
					<li>Laboratory and service equipment shop drawing review</li>
				</ul>
			</li><li>CL3 operation protocol review with User Group and Biosafety Officer</li>
			<li>Chairing regular commissioning meetings during commissioning and certification project phase</li>
			<li>Construction trades coordination and activities sequence scheduling with respect to testing and acceptance of the containment envelope, services penetrations and services finishes</li>
			<li>Construction review and site inspection of the CL3 laboratory</li>
			<li>Pressure decay testing for CL3 lab ductwork and HEPA filters housing assemblies with the Sheet Metal Contractor</li>
			<li>Commissioning of all building systems associated with CL3 laboratories</li>
			<li>Manage, coordinate and participate in the certification process</li>
			<li>Preparation of user manuals for CL3 laboratories</li>
			<li>Preparation, assembly and submission of the final certification report in line with the Federal Biosafety Standards</li>
			<li>Demonstration and validation of laboratory systems operation and fail safe containment integrity in front of federal biosafety officials</li>
		</ol>
